values: Charlene has a fantasy. She returns to the North Country to live on an island ... Isle-au-Haut ... off the coast of Maine. Her husband is a lobsterman and goes out all day in the summer time and comes home at night to be with her and the children. He smells of saltwater and wind. Charlene has her consulting office in the back of her beachside home, with an English Garden outside of it and pansies in the window box. She does therapy with her clients, where they can see the sea outside her windows, and Charlene can see her children running on the beach. At lunch time, the children, two girls and a boy with sunkissed curly dark hair and their father's ocean eyes, run to her and give her kisses and crab shells. She herds them inside to her dining room with the picture window and the four Maine Coon cats wandering the grounds. Lunch is deviled ham sandwiches. After more clients and hours at the beach for the children, Charlene's husband comes home for night. On the cool evenings, they sometimes light a fire with the pine logs piled beside the house that the children chopped.

She sits,
poised,
tail curved around her pale white paws
casting a shadow
illusion

green eyes sharp
sniffing the air 
in the soft spring dark
ready to creep 
silently

with her sole
lunar companion
illuminating 
her path

Bed

I preclude the possibility of "bed" by not making it.  In a strange 
sort of way, an unmade bed equals unfulfilled desire; and therefore, 
because the bed is unmade, I will reasonably not let you take me home, and 
therefore will not invite you in to meet Claire, and you, by the same 
sort of strange reasoning, will not say yes.  Saying yes implies certain 
other things, and when I step aside to put the water on to boil, you 
will not have a chance to pick out the Harry Connick, Jr. CD or the one 
entitled "Jazz for the Quiet Times" and put it on to play softly in the 
background.  You will not have a chance to remark on the niceness of 
the place, nor will you have a chance for your grin to turn serious and 
to put your arms around me and kiss me fully on the lips.
I will not have swept the floor of kitty littler so neither of us will 
have to bother stepping on it with bare feet.  Nor will I have set out 
the bar soap -- a subtle and discreet sign of premeditation.  You won't 
have the chance to hear me grunt softly and learn firsthand that I'm 
not nearly as proper as you think I am.  You won't bury your face in my 
hair on the embroidered pillowcase and I won't feel your breath on the 
side of my face like that day you were close enough for me to feel it in 
my hair.  I won't stay you when you make a move to leave, and you won't 
share the bed that's too big for just me.  I won't wake up to the 
daylight, and you won't find out that my clockradio is set to NPR.  
So I think we'll continue to tiptoe around eachother, with long looks 
and shared smiles.  At least, that is, until you say yes because the bar 
soap has been set out.
And the bed is made.

Chasing the Dream

Watching you across the room, so familiar but so brand new. I remember those chance encounters, and I look in your eyes so dark so deep... I cannot disguise myself.  
Golden angel, I cannot deny I've fallen. 
Forbidden devil, you are my wings. 
In another time in another place there'd be a day I'd have you in for coffee. You wear that shirt and I'll wear that necklace. Chiseled features in the dark take me in, I know they do, that way you have of staring yet not being caught in the act. I dare you to look with others around; I still smile and you offer me yours. 
You're rather tall next to me - I hadn't noticed until today when I smelled your essence. I remember your jacket with the button cuffs that smelled the same way. 
I want to feel your lips on mine and feel you touch my collarbone. I'll hold your face while trying to control my instant blush. Aren't I obvious? Your whispering chime of an entrancing voice makes me want to run into your arms but shut the door behind us. I want to hold you close and hear your heartbeat... fall in love with you. 
Come, and we'll walk through the dark; watch the frost glitter in the moonlight. Taste the wood smoke in the air and feel the waves breaking on the beach. Show me those stars you promised so long ago. Let the wind on your fingers blow through my hair; sit by a fireplace and melt in the flames. I hesitate to call you my love and I hesitate to whisper in your ear. I am just a baby next to you... so innocent. Yet you've seen my still waters run deep. I know you see me! Just the way you stand. 
I dare not say a thing because you are untouchable, so attainable. But at night I'll visit these peaceful meadows with you as my phantom companion; wrap my arms around tomorrow and continue chasing the dream.
